To make the title and other elements of the Gradio interface more colorful, you can use custom CSS styles. Gradio allows you to apply custom styles to the interface by specifying a CSS string in the `css` parameter of the `Interface` class. Here's how you can customize your Gradio interface with colorful styles:

```python
...
# Define custom CSS to apply color to the title and interface elements
custom_css = """
h1 {
    color: #3772FF; /* Change title color */
    text-align: center;
}

/* Style for the interface description text */
p {
    color: #3772FF;
    text-align: center;
}

/* Style for radio button labels */
.gr-radio label {
    color: #3772FF;
}

/* Customize Gradio text input and output */
.gr-textbox, .output-html .gr-html-container {
    border: 2px solid #3772FF;
}

/* Button color customization through hover */
button:hover {
    background-color: #3772FF !important;
    color: white !important;
}

/* Active radio button customization */
input[type='radio']:checked + label {
    background-color: #3772FF;
    border-color: #3772FF;
    color: white;
}
"""

# Define Gradio interface with CSS
iface = gr.Interface(
    fn=fetch_details,
    inputs=[
        gr.Textbox(label="Enter PR_Number (leave blank if using status filter)"),
        gr.Radio(choices=["Submitted", "Ordered", "Composing"], label="User Status")
    ],
    outputs="html",
    title="Procure Status Management",
    description="Enter PR_Number or choose a status to fetch details:",
    theme="compact",
    css=custom_css  # Include custom CSS
)

# Launch the Gradio interface
iface.launch()
```

